00:11:02.380 --> 00:11:05.200
they were pretty much
done treating her acne.

00:11:05.200 --> 00:11:06.930
And I wanna know how
many people in this room

00:11:06.930 --> 00:11:08.453
had acne as teenagers?

00:11:09.720 --> 00:11:12.640
So, it's not just a cosmetic problem.

00:11:12.640 --> 00:11:15.160
It is uncomfortable, it hurts,

00:11:15.160 --> 00:11:17.148
and this mother was
advocating for her child

00:11:17.148 --> 00:11:18.330
to have a more aggressive therapy,

00:11:18.330 --> 00:11:20.070
and we teamed up and you'll see what we,

00:11:20.070 --> 00:11:21.900
what we did for her ultimately.

00:11:21.900 --> 00:11:25.080
But she could not get access
to dermatology in her community

00:11:25.080 --> 00:11:26.933
and she drove a ways to see me.

00:11:28.470 --> 00:11:31.380
There's pain, there's scarring,
there's disfigurement.

00:11:31.380 --> 00:11:33.910
And these are true issues that
need to be treated seriously.

00:11:33.910 --> 00:11:36.130
It's not just "cosmetic."

00:11:36.130 --> 00:11:37.830
But there is a problem
with access to care,

00:11:37.830 --> 00:11:39.870
to dermatology, specialty care.

